summary: The document is a part of the records released under the President John F. Kennedy Assassination Records Act of 1992, specifically an FBI document related to the JFK assassination system. It includes administrative details, classification information, and references to individuals and events possibly connected to the assassination. The document is marked as 'Secret' and contains information shared with the United States Customs Office, Miami, in September 1958. It references individuals such as RENALDO BLANCO HERNANDEZ and ALBERTO EUSEBIO MOJENA, and includes details about telephonic information and reports from various dates in 1958.
key_findings: Document is part of the JFK assassination records released in 2025 under the 1992 Act.
Marked as 'Secret' with restrictions and last reviewed in 1998.
References individuals and events potentially linked to the JFK assassination.
Includes information shared with the United States Customs Office, Miami, in September 1958.
Contains details about telephonic information and reports from 1958.
